  "prompt": "Why do I see numbers and not contacts' names? In WhatsApp?",
  "response": "If you're seeing numbers instead of contact names in WhatsApp, it could be due to a few reasons:\n\n1. **Contact Not Saved**: The number in question may not be saved in your phone's contacts. WhatsApp pulls information from your contacts, so ensure the number is saved.\n\n2. **Sync Issues**: There might be a syncing problem between your contacts and WhatsApp. Try refreshing the contacts in WhatsApp by going to the contact tab, tapping the three dots (or options menu) in the top corner, and selecting \"Refresh\".\n\n3. **Permissions**: WhatsApp needs access to your contacts. Ensure that the app has the necessary permissions:\n   - **Android**: Go to `Settings > Apps > WhatsApp > Permissions`, and ensure \"Contacts\" is enabled.\n   - **iPhone**: Go to `Settings > Privacy > Contacts`, and make sure WhatsApp has access.\n\n4. **App Version**: Ensure you are using the latest version of WhatsApp. An outdated app can cause glitches. Check the Google Play Store (for Android) or the App Store (for iPhone) for updates.\n\n5. **Data Saving Mode**: If you're using any data-saving modes or restrictions, they might be affecting WhatsApp's ability to display contact names.\n\n6. **Reinstall WhatsApp**: If all else fails, you might consider reinstalling WhatsApp. Remember to back up your chats before doing this.\n\nIf you've checked all of these and still see numbers instead of names, it may be worth contacting WhatsApp support for further assistance.",
